{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{infobox government agency | agency_name = Department for Exiting the European Union | type = department | seal = | logo = Department_for_Exiting_the_European_Union_Logo.png | formed = 14 July 2016 | jurisdiction = United Kingdom | headquarters = [[9 Downing Street]], London, England<ref name="DExEU - GOV.UK">{{cite web|title=Department for Exiting the European Union|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-exiting-the-european-union|website=GOV.UK|date=3 August 2016|accessdate=3 August 2016}}</ref> | employees = | budget = | minister1_name = [[Stephen Barclay]] | minister1_pfo = [[Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union]] | chief1_name = [[Philip Rycroft]] | chief1_position = Permanent Secretary | child1_agency = | region_code = GB | website = [https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-exiting-the-european-union Official website] }}
The '''Department for Exiting the European Union''' ('''DExEU'''; also known as the '''Brexit Department''')<ref name="DExEU - GOV.UK" /> is the [[government department]] of the [[United Kingdom]] responsible for overseeing negotiations relating to the [[Brexit|United Kingdom's withdrawal from the European Union]] and establishing the future relationship between the United Kingdom and the EU.<ref name="DExEU - GOV.UK" /> It was formed by the Prime Minister, [[Theresa May]], in July 2016, in the wake of the [[United Kingdom European Union membership referendum, 2016|referendum vote to leave the European Union]].<ref name="csw new article">{{cite web|url=https://www.civilserviceworld.com/articles/news/theresa-may-signals-whitehall-rejig-two-new-cabinet-posts|title=Theresa May signals Whitehall rejig with two new Cabinet posts|last=|first=|date=|website=Civil Service World|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref>
The department was formed by combining staff from the [[Cabinet Office]]’s Europe Unit, the Europe Directorate of the [[Foreign and Commonwealth Office]], and the United Kingdom's [[Committee of Permanent Representatives|Permanent Representation to the EU]], and may take on staff from other government departments as necessary.<ref name="Hansard HCWS94">{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2016-07-18/HCWS94|title=Machinery of Government Changes:Written statement - HCWS94|last=|first=|date=18 July 2016|website=Hansard|publisher=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=22 July 2016}}</ref> The department was overseen by [[David Davis (British politician)|David Davis]] MP, until he resigned on 8 July 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Rayner |first1=Gordon |title=David Davis resigns as Brexit secretary |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/07/08/david-davis-resigns-brexit-secretary/ |accessdate=8 July 2018 |work=The Daily Telegraph |date=8 July 2018}}</ref><ref name="resignation">{{cite news |title=Brexit Secretary David Davis resigns |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-44761056 |work=BBC News |date=9 July 2018}}</ref> [[Dominic Raab]] was appointed as [[Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union]] on 9 July 2018,<ref>{{cite news|authors=Dan Sabbagh and Jessica Elgot |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/jul/09/dominic-raab-appointed-new-brexit-secretary-in-uk-cabinet-reshuffle |title=Dominic Raab named Brexit secretary in cabinet reshuffle |work=The Guardian |date=9 July 2018 |accessdate=12 October 2018}}</ref> but resigned on 15 November 2018 over the draft withdrawal agreement.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-46219495 |title=Brexit Secretary Dominic Raab resigns over EU agreement |work=[[BBC News]]|date= 15 November 2018 |access-date=15 November 2018}}</ref> His replacement was announced on 16 November 2018 to be [[Stephen Barclay]].<ref name=Barclay>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Stephen Barclay named new Brexit Secretary |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-46241693 |work=[[BBC News]] |date=16 November 2018 |access-date=16 November 2018}}</ref>
