The [[Permanent Secretary]] at the Department for Exiting the European Union was [[Oliver Robbins]]. In September 2017, Robbins left the Department as the prime minister appointed him the EU adviser in the Cabinet Office.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.civilserviceworld.com/articles/news/oliver-robbins-leaves-dexeu-lead-cross-government-brexit-coordination-number-10 |title=Oliver Robbins leaves DExEU to lead cross-government Brexit coordination in Number 10 |last=Johnstone |first=Richard |date=18 September 2017 |website=Civil Service World |archive-url= |archive-date= |dead-url=no |access-date=13 October 2017 }}</ref> In October 2017, [[Philip Rycroft]] was appointed the new Permanent Secretary,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/people/philip-rycroft |title=Philip Rycroft |website=GOV.UK |archive-url= |archive-date= |dead-url=no |access-date=13 October 2017 }}</ref> having previously been the Department's Second Permanent Secretary.
== Staff == In March 2018 government data stated the Department had 636 full-time equivalent posts,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/702838/WFMR_Mar_18_DExEU.csv_-_WFMR_Mar_18_DExEU.csv_-_WFMR_Mar_18_DExEU.csv.csv.csv/preview|title=DExEU monthly workforce management information: March 2018}}</ref> rising to 651 in August 2018 (excluding contractors, management consultants and faststreamers<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/744002/WFMR_Aug_18_DExEU_-_WFMR_Aug_18_DExEU.csv/preview|title=DExEU monthly workforce management information: August 2018 - GOV.UK|website=www.gov.uk|language=en|access-date=11 October 2018}}</ref>) on an average (mean) monthy wage of £5,890 including allowances.
