==Theme song== Since 2000 every drupa had its own theme song. The idea started in 1986 with a song featuring a country folk style which was later nominated as one of the worst corporate anthems ever by ''[[The Register]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2005/11/28/anthem_poll/ |title=Vote now for the worst corporate anthem - ever! |publisher=[[The Register]] |accessdate=17 October 2014}}</ref> Nevertheless, they are one of the drupa trademarks since the theme song concept was resurrected with a dance/pop power ballad in 2000. The drupa 2004 theme song used a techno dance style while the song for 2012 was performed by Dirk Zeisler.
